wner_createdAt`\n   - `steps.by_owner_updatedAt`\n   - `steps.by_owner_videoHash` if the schema supports indexing extracted hashes directly; otherwise implement duplicate lookup by owner query.\n   - `practiceSessions.by_owner`\n   - `practiceSessions.by_owner_createdAt`\n\nTracer/phase plan:\n\n1. Tracer: add minimal `steps` + `practiceSessions` schema, owner indexes, Convex validates.\n2. Expand validators: video, practice/view records, difficulty, kind, timestamps, GCS object keys.\n3. Add feed/session/migration indexes; export inferred/shared types only if needed.\n4. Tighten tests/imports.\n\nLikely files:\n\n- Modify `convex/schema.ts`.\n- Create `convex/model/validators.ts` if validators are too large for the schema file.\n- Create `convex/model/types.ts` for shared inferred types if useful.\n- `convex/schema.ts`\n- `convex/model/validators.ts`\n- `convex/model/types.ts`\n- `tests/convex-schema.test.ts`\n\nVerification:\n\nRun:\n\n```bash\nnpm run typecheck\nnpm run lint\nnpx convex dev --once\n```\n\nExpected:\n\n- Convex accepts the schema.\n- TypeScript can import generated table types without errors.\n\nUnresolved questions:\n\n- Should `videoHash` be denormalized for indexing, or is owner query scan acceptable?\n\nSource files:\n\n- Task: .agents/tasks/2 - data model and migrations/1 - define convex schema and indexes.md\n- Plan: .agents/tasks/2 - data model and migrations/1 - define convex schema and indexes.plan.md\n- Context: .agents/tasks/2 - data model and migrations/context.md",
